    <h1>Content Repository configuration</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1485852738438 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1485852738438 ul {list-style: disc;margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1485852738438 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style></p>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1485852738438">=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Configurationexamples">Confi=
guration examples</a>=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Usingdefaultvalues">Using de=
fault values</a></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Allexplicit">All explicit</a=
></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Legacystorageengine">Legacy =
storage engine</a></li>=20
</ul> </li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Field_groups_configurationFi=
eldgroupsconfiguration">Field groups configuration</a></li>=20
</ul>=20
</div>
<p></p>
<p>The <strong>content repository</strong> is where all your content is bee=
n stored. It is the heart of eZ Platform which you interact with using Publ=
ic API.</p>
<p>To store data, the content repository <strong>uses a storage engine</str=
ong> that can virtually can work with any kind of storage (RDBMS, NoSQL, et=
c.). eZ Publish 5 came with a relational storage engine, compatible with v4=
.x: the <strong>Legacy storage engine</strong>, which is the default.</p>
<p>You can define several repositories within a single application. However=
, you can only use one per site.</p>
<h2 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Configurationexamples">Configurati=
on examples</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Usingdefaultvalues">Using default =
values</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezplatform.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    repositories:
        # Defining repository with alias "main"
        # Default storage engine is used, with default connection
        # Equals to:
        # main: { engine: legacy, connection: &lt;defaultConnectionName&gt;=
 }
        main: ~

    system:
        # All members of my_siteaccess_group will use "main" repository
        # No need to set "repository", it will take the first defined repos=
itory by default
        my_siteaccess_group:
            # ...</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If no repository is specified for a siteaccess or siteaccess group, the =
first defined repository (under <code>ezpublish.repositories</code>) will b=
e used.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Allexplicit">All explicit</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezplatform.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">doctrine:
    dbal:
        default_connection: my_connection_name
        connections:
            my_connection_name:
                driver:   pdo_mysql
                host:     localhost
                port:     3306
                dbname:   my_database
                user:     my_user
                password: my_password
                charset:  UTF8

            another_connection_name:
                # ...

ezpublish:
    repositories:
        first_repository: { engine: legacy, connection: my_connection_name,=
 config: {} }
        second_repository: { engine: legacy, connection: another_connection=
_name, config: {} }

    # ...

    system:
        my_first_siteaccess:
            repository: first_repository

            # ...

        my_second_siteaccess:
            repository: second_repository</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Legacystorageengine">Legacy storag=
e engine</h3>
<p><span>Legacy storage engine uses <a href=3D"http://docs.doctrine-project=
.org/projects/doctrine-dbal/en/latest/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">Doctrine DBAL</a> (Database Abstraction Layer). Database settings are=
 supplied by <a href=3D"https://github.com/doctrine/DoctrineBundle" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">DoctrineBundle</a>. As such, you can re=
fer to <a href=3D"https://github.com/doctrine/DoctrineBundle/blob/master/Re=
sources/doc/configuration.rst#doctrine-dbal-configuration" class=3D"externa=
l-link" rel=3D"nofollow">DoctrineBundle's documentation</a>.</span></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title">ORM</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Doctrine ORM is <strong>not</strong> provided by default. If you want to=
 use it, you will need to add <code>doctrine/orm</code> as a dependency in =
your <code>composer.json</code>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><span><br></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Field_groups_configurationFieldgro=
upsconfiguration"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"ContentRepos=
itoryconfiguration-Field_groups_configuration"></span>Field groups configur=
ation</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-error">SINCE 1.3/16.=
04</span></p>
<p>Field groups, used in content and Content Type editing, can be configure=
d from the repository section. Values entered there are field group <em>ide=
ntifiers</em>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">repositories:
  default:
    fields_groups:
      list: [content, features, metadata]
      default: content</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>These identifiers can be given human-readable values and translated. Tho=
se values will at the moment be used when editing Content Types. The transl=
ation domain is&nbsp;<code>ezplatform_fields_groups</code>.<br>This file wi=
ll define English names for field groups:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>app/Resources/translations/ezplatform_fields_groups.en.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">content: Content
metadata: Metadata
user_data: User data</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
    </div>
